<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-599] AbstractMatrix uses clone() where it should use like()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-599</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The AbstractMatrix.java class uses clone() instead of like() in the methods which create a new matrix and populate it with calculated data. This means that the contents of &apos;this&apos; is copied into the return matrix, then promptly overwritten.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch fixes this problem by substituting like() and changing the code to not rely on having the values of &apos;this&apos; in the clone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, this allows generated matrices like a random matrix to reuse the code from AbstractMatrix; read-only matrices cannot populate their clones.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
